reviews.text:
Very cramped space with most of the owners buddies and himself taking up 4-6 seats.; they weren’t even doing anything except talking on the phone.
Service was real slow despite not being crowded. It’s a real disappointment that they had to behave in this way. 
Other Turkish outlets have so much faster service. 
The owner occasionally stands outside and drinks tea; looking at his customers waiting for food. Strange, that nothing appeared to make him improve his service. 
When the food finally came; it was average at best. 
Once two of his buddies finished eating; they started to smoke right at the entrance of the restaurant. With a fan near the entrance blowing all the smoke in at other patrons.
I wish it was a better experience.
Great authentic Turkish food. A clear recommendation from me. My favourite is the Dürüm Kebab. You get a round Kebab to eat. Good for to go.

They served only halal. No alcohol allowed
